events.html: • 1887 – The United States receives rights to Pearl Harbor, Hawaii.

events.description: The Cullinan Diamond is presented to King Edward VII on his birthday.

events.description: The National Fascist Party (Partito Nazionale Fascista or PNF) is founded in Italy.
events.html: • 1921 – The National Fascist Party (Partito Nazionale Fascista or PNF) is founded in Italy.[19][20]

events.description: In Munich, police and government troops crush the Nazi Beer Hall Putsch.
events.html: • 1923 – In Munich, police and government troops crush the Nazi Beer Hall Putsch.

events.html: • 1935 – The Committee for Industrial Organization, the precursor to the Congress of Industrial Organizations, is founded in Atlantic City, New Jersey, by eight trade unions belonging to the American Federation of Labor.[21]

events.html: • 1938 – Kristallnacht occurs, instigated by the Nazis using the killing of German diplomat Ernst vom Rath by Herschel Grynszpan as justification.

events.description: Warsaw is awarded the Virtuti Militari by the Polish government-in-exile.
events.html: • 1940 – Warsaw is awarded the Virtuti Militari by the Polish government-in-exile.

events.html: • 1942 – Battle of Stalingrad: German forces of the 6th Army under general Friedrich Paulus reach finally the river bank of the Volga, capturing 90% of the ruined city of Stalingrad and splitting the remaining Soviet forces into two narrow pockets.[23]

events.html: • 1953 – Cambodia gains independence from France.

events.html: • 1960 – Robert McNamara is named president of the Ford Motor Company, becoming the first non-Ford family member to serve in that post. He resigns a month later to join the newly elected John F. Kennedy administration.

events.html: • 1963 – At a coal mine in Miike, Japan, an explosion kills 458 and hospitalises 839 with carbon monoxide poisoning.
